      <profileDesc>
         <particDesc>
            <listPerson>
               <person>
                  <p>The commissioner was ˀabunä ˁAynä Krǝstos mentioned in the supplication formulas (see fol. <locus target="#125"/>
                     <locus from="136rb"/>va, where also his relatives and disciples are recalled; see also the Miracles). The manuscript was originally in possession of the monastery on the island of Mǝṣraḥa on Lake Ṭana (see Pankhurst <locus target="#1973"/>:<locus target="#15"/>), where ˀabunä ˁAynä Krǝstos could have been the abbot. </p>
                  <p>The manuscript was possibly one of those taken to Mäqdäla by King Tewodros II (r. <locus from="1856" to="68"/>) even though it lacks the typical possession note referring to the church Mäqdäla Mädḫane ˁAläm. The troops of the Napier Expedition captured Mäqdäla on <locus target="#13"/>April <locus target="#1868"/>. Does the note on fol. <locus target="#1a"/>indicate that G. Lents got the book in his possession <locus target="#13"/>April <locus target="#1868"/>? (on the fate of the books from Mäqdäla Mädḫane ˁAläm, see the recent Ancel – Nosnitsin <locus target="#2014"/>).</p>
                  
               </person>
            </listPerson>
         </particDesc>
